nstrate the effects of venom - and the often erratic impact of 'cures'. In exploring this culture of colonial vivisection, Venomous Encounters asks fundamental questions about human-animal relationships and the nature of modern medicine.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aPoisonous snakesxVenomzAustraliaxHistory. 0aVenomzAustraliaxHistory. 0aVivisectionzAustraliaxHistory. 4aStudies in Imperialism 2017. 7aHISTORY / Australia & New Zealand.2bisacsh  aBritish legislation.  aamoral ascent.  aanimal experiments.  acolonial Australia.  acolonial animal matrix.  acolonial antipodes.  acolonial vivisection.  aenvenomation.  aimmunology.  aplebian expertise.  apublic spectacles.  ascientific medicine.  asnakebite antidotes.  asnakebitten dog.  avenomus encounters.1 aHobbins, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2017 eBook-Packagez978311128281740uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152610627840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526106278423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526106278/original  a978-3-11-128281-7  Manchester University Press 2017 eBook-Packageb2017  aGBV-deGruyter-alles